==English==
===Etymology===
Usage began in the first half of the 1900s.
===Idiom===
'''[[price]] out of [[market]]'''
# To [[charge]] an [[exorbitant]] price for a service or product so that no one will [[purchase]] it.
#: ''He's pricing out of market, asking for $100,000 for that shack!''
